title: The One Where No One Proposes
synopsis: Because of a misunderstanding, Rachel finds herself engaged to Joey instead of Ross, who was planning to propose.

title: The One Where Emma Cries
synopsis: Somebody ends up in the hospital when Joey attempts to apologize to Ross for mistakenly asking Rachel to marry him.

title: The One with the Pediatrician
synopsis: Rachel's constant calls to Emma's pediatrician force him to reject her as a patient.

title: The One with the Sharks
synopsis: Phoebe fears losing Mike, and her self-doubt is exacerbated by Ross' foolish comments.

title: The One with Phoebe's Birthday Dinner
synopsis: Rachel is afraid to leave Emma with a babysitter.

title: The One with the Male Nanny
synopsis: Ross jealously mocks Rachel's choice of an oversensitive male nanny for Emma.

title: The One with Ross' Inappropriate Song
synopsis: When Chandler's former romantic rival decides to sell his apartment, Chandler persuades Joey to help him inspect it on the sly.

title: The One with Rachel's Other Sister
synopsis: Rachel's self-centered younger sister, Amy, ruins everyone's Thanksgiving dinner with her uncensored observations.

title: The One with Rachel's Phone Number
synopsis: While on a night out with Phoebe, Rachel impulsively gives her telephone number to a handsome restaurant patron.

title: The One with Christmas in Tulsa
synopsis: Because of a critical deadline at work, Chandler is stuck spending Christmas in Tulsa, Okla.

title: The One Where Rachel Goes Back to Work
synopsis: While visiting her workplace to show off baby Emma, Rachel is surprised to find a handsome temp who's been doing her job.

title: The One with Phoebe's Rats
synopsis: Rachel is irritated to learn that her handsome workplace rival has been invited to her birthday party.

title: The One Where Monica Sings
synopsis: While Rachel sorts out her conflicted feelings for Gavin, Ross sets out to make her jealous, enlisting Chandler to help him meet attractive women.

title: The One with the Blind Dates
synopsis: In an attempt to reunite Rachel and Ross, Joey and Phoebe arrange awful blind dates for both of them.

title: The One with the Mugging
synopsis: Joey develops an unusual acting method to impress a famous fellow actor. Meanwhile, Chandler accepts an internship at an advertising agency.

title: The One with the Boob Job
synopsis: Phoebe asks Mike to move in with her, but coming so close to married life may cause trouble in their relationship.

title: The One with the Memorial Service
synopsis: When Chandler jokingly posts an outrageous biography about Ross on his college alumni Web site, Ross retaliates.

title: The One with the Lottery
synopsis: Hoping to win a huge jackpot, the friends pool their money and buy dozens of lottery tickets.

title: The One with Rachel's Dream
synopsis: Nervous because his daytime-drama role requires him to act as if he's deeply in love with a woman, Joey rehearses with Rachel.

title: The One with the Soap Opera Party
synopsis: Ross is excited when he meets fellow paleontologist Charlie Wheeler, who's a stunning beauty.

title: The One with the Fertility Test
synopsis: Ross is in agony because Charlie is dating Joey. Meanwhile, Chandler and Monica visit a fertility clinic.

title: The One with the Donor
synopsis: Disappointed to learn that they can't conceive a baby naturally, Monica and Chandler consider their options.

title: The One in Barbados
synopsis: The gang accompanies Ross to a paleontology convention in Barbados, where Ross bonds with Charlie while Joey and Rachel get drunk together.
